{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, quantitative reasoning contains more difficult problems, as the model has to provide a complete and self-contained solution without relying on external tools (Shao et al., 2024; Lin et al., 2024b).",
    "We see a dominance of use from GSM8K and MATH for QA, and from MathQA and Math23K for MWP.",
    "For quantitative reasoning, MMLU-STEM (Hendrycks et al., 2021a) and Big-Bench Hard (Suzgun et al., 2023) are the most widely adopted.",
    "Geometry is one of the most important branches of mathematics, and it expresses the settings jointly in text and diagrams.",
    "As such, it is mandatory to involve the vision modality for geometry LLMs."
  ]
}